18#include "ZXContainerAlgorithms.h"
19
20#include <algorithm>
21#include <cassert>
22#include <vector>
23
24namespace ZXing {
25
26template <class T>
27class Matrix
28{
29public:
30 using value_t = T;
31
32private:
33 int _width = 0;
34 int _height = 0;
35 std::vector<value_t> _data;
36
37 // Nothing wrong to support it, just to make it explicit, instead of by mistake.
38 // Use copy() below.
39 Matrix(const Matrix &) = default;
40 Matrix& operator=(const Matrix &) = delete;
41
42public:
43 Matrix() = default;
44 Matrix(int width, int height, value_t val = {}) : _width(width), _height(height), _data(_width * _height, val) { }
45
46 Matrix(Matrix&&) = default;
47 Matrix& operator=(Matrix&&) = default;
48
49 Matrix copy() const {
50 return *this;
51 }
52
53 int height() const {
54 return _height;
55 }
56
57 int width() const {
58 return _width;
59 }
60
61 int size() const {
62 return Size(_data);
63 }
64
65 value_t& operator()(int x, int y)
66 {
67 assert(x >= 0 && x < _width && y >= 0 && y < _height);
68 return _data[y * _width + x];
69 }
70
71 const T& operator()(int x, int y) const
72 {
73 assert(x >= 0 && x < _width && y >= 0 && y < _height);
74 return _data[y * _width + x];
75 }
76
77 const value_t& get(int x, int y) const {
78 return operator()(x, y);
79 }
80
81 void set(int x, int y, value_t value) {
82 operator()(x, y) = value;
83 }
84
85 const value_t* data() const {
86 return _data.data();
87 }
88
89 const value_t* begin() const {
90 return _data.data();
91 }
92
93 const value_t* end() const {
94 return _data.data() + _width * _height;
95 }
96
97 void clear(value_t value = {}) {
98 std::fill(_data.begin(), _data.end(), value);
99 }
100};
101
102} // ZXing
